title: Firangi
subTitle: Inspired by the life of Indian cricketer and former captain of the Indian national team, Mohammad Azharuddin. A talented young cricketer rises to prominence but finds his career threatened by accusations of match-fixing. 'Azhar' stars Emraan Hashmi, Lara Dutta and Nargis Fakhri.

title: No Parking (Hindi)
subTitle: A young man's dual identity as an adopted son and a hired killer creates turmoil when he faces an impossible choice that unravels his life. The action-comedy film stars Vijay, Sanghavi and Jaishankar.

title: Darr@ The Mall
subTitle: A newly built mall becomes shrouded in mystery as several workers die mysteriously during construction. A security guard unravels the haunting secret behind the mall's dark past. The horror movie stars Jimmy Sheirgill, Nushratt Bharucha, Arif Zakaria and Asif Basra.

title: No Parking
subTitle: Arun is an architect who has a loving mother, and a beautiful girlfriend. Things go haywire when he parks his bike in a &quot;No Parking&quot; zone. This takes him on a roller coaster ride full of lies and deceit.

title: Charms Bond
subTitle: Hilarity ensues when a young man, his cousin and a friend hatch a plan to steal money from his miserly step-mother. 'Charms Bond' stars Priya Anand, Yogi Babu and Mirchi Shiva.

title: Lucifer
subTitle: After the death of the ruling party's supreme leader in God's own country, a power vaccuum gives rise to unprecedent forces in the chaos for succession, impacting both the party and state. The 2019 Malayalam blockbuster Lucifer stars Mohanlal, Vivek Oberois and Manju Warrier.

title: Baadshah Pehlwaan
subTitle: Krishna is an orphan who is being brought up by a gym owner whose name is Sarkar. Krishna beats the odds to become a Baadshah Pehlwaan, but when he falls in love, he gets into a dispute with himself.

title: Ek Ka Dum 1
subTitle: A young musician with a psychological disorder is convinced that three men murdered his parents. However, he is unable to identify any of them. Will he be able to get to the bottom of the mystery? '1: Ek Ka Dum' stars Mahesh Babu, Kriti Sanon, Nassar, Pradeep Rawat and Kelly Dorji.

title: The Real Leader Brahma
subTitle: A feared gangster escapes the cops and heads on a covert mission to Malaysia, where, he encounters a woman who falls for him. Upon his return to India, she follows him, leading to a tale of unraveling secrets, missions and a link to a 16th-century warrior. Can the police apprehend him for his crimes? The action-drama stars Upendra, Pranitha Subhash, Sara Sharmaa, Nasser and Sayaji Shinde.

title: Gunda Mawali
subTitle: A beautiful woman and an auto driver fake a romantic relationship to deter suitors, but their plan backfires as they unexpectedly develop real feelings for each other. The romantic-drama movie stars Nagarjuna, Deepti Bhatnagar, Simran and Dara Singh.

title: Firangi
subTitle: Set in the 1920s, the undisputed King of Comedy Kapil Sharma plays a young man with the unique ability to cure backaches with a kick. However, the family of the girl he wants to marry rejects his proposal as he serves the very people against whom they have been fighting for independence. 'Firangi' also stars Ishita Dutta and Monica Gill.

title: TE3N
subTitle: Based on the 2013 South Korean film 'Montage', the mystery-thriller follows a 70-year-old man on a quest to unravel the truth of what happened to his granddaughter. He enlists the help of a priest and a police officer to find the people who kidnapped and killed her. 'Te3n' stars Amitabh Bachchan, Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Sabyasachi Chakraborty, Padmavati Rao and Vidya Balan.

title: Badava Rascal
subTitle: Kidnapped by thugs, a young man captivates his captors with the story of his life to compel them to second-guess their choices. The action-comedy movie stars Amrutha Iyengar, Rangayana Raghu, Nagabhushan and Tara.

title: Ab Tak Chhappan 2
subTitle: The sequel to Ab Tak Chhappan' follows a retired encounter specialist who returns to Mumbai to face a storm of criminal challenges, testing his skills to the limit. 'Ab Tak Chhappan 2' stars Nana Patekar, Ashutosh Rana, Vikram Gokhale, Gul Panag, Dr Mohan Agashe, Tanmay Jahagirdar, Dilip Prabhavalkar, Revathi and Govind Namdev.

title: Soorma
subTitle: Based on the life of hockey legend Sandeep Singh, 'Soorma' is a story of determination, hard work and love for the sport. When the upcoming hockey player is accidentally shot and left paralysed, he decides to do whatever it takes to overcome his disability so he can lead the Indian team to victory. The movie stars Diljit Dosanjh, Taapsee Pannu, Angad Bedi and Vijay Raaz.

title: Main Hoon Lucky The Racer
subTitle: Main Hoon Lucky The Racer is all about two brothers who do things differently. While one brother follows rules and regulations, the other tries to achieve it in his own unique way.
